<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862T.01/561½</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a
                                Conversation with the German Ambassador</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Wiedfeldt</hi>), <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1923</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1923-01-23">January 23, 1923</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <p>The German Ambassador said that in view of the departure of the American
                            forces from Germany today his Government had <pb facs="0317" n="193" xml:id="pg_193"/> instructed him to express to the Secretary the
                            sincere thanks of the German Government for the correct conduct of the
                            American troops during the time of occupation.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>